{
  "stem": "3874.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was a perfectly safe city at the time to run around in, so we had, I had a great time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the train trip itself was not-- was not very traumatic, really.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, there were 50 of us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were some kids-- there were children as young as five or six years old.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the oldest was 12.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Since then, I've read many articles and books about the situation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The children who-- they picked children of certain ages, because they felt they were the most vulnerable-- well, they were the most vulnerable, and still the French organizations were going to be able to take care of them.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For instance, they wouldn't take babies-- so people who couldn't-- kids who couldn't feed themselves, people who had sicknesses, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They also felt that-- that children over 13 were big enough that they could manage better on their own, if they had to, than children under that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that's why, I guess, they picked these particular age group to send them on the children's transport.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, the English, I think they took children up to the age of about 15 or 16.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But the two transports that left Austria from Vienna, they only took them up to about the age of 12-- up to 12, up to and including the age of 12.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember we arrived and-- and some kids were crying, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I was not particularly unhappy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I was leaving Austria, I was leaving a situation which was-- which was already getting pretty bad.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You know-- I don't like to get beaten up in school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I couldn't go outside and play anymore, because you'd always be afraid that the Hitler Youth gangs would come along.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
